{
	"info": {
		"name": "POS System",
		"description": "Point of Sale System API\n\n## Authentication\nMost endpoints require a Bearer token. Use the **Login** request to get a token, which is automatically stored in the `token` collection variable via the test script.\n\n## Purchase Immutability Rules\n- A purchase is created in **draft** status.\n- While **draft**: header can be updated, items can be added/updated/deleted.\n- On **complete**: inventory records + stock movements are created, status becomes `completed`.\n- Once **completed**: the purchase is **immutable**. No edits, no status changes.\n- **Cancel** is only allowed for **draft** purchases.\n- All business rule violations return `HTTP 400` with a `DomainException` message.\n\n## Inventory Rules\n- `inventory_items` and `inventory_quantities` are **read-only** APIs.\n- `stock_movements` is **read-only**, created automatically by services.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "base_url",
			"value": "http://localhost:8000/api",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "token",
			"value": "",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "purchase_id",
			"value": "1",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "item_id",
			"value": "1",
			"type": "string"
		}
	],
	"auth": {
		"type": "bearer",
		"bearer": [
			{
				"key": "token",
				"value": "{{token}}",
				"type": "string"
			}
		]
	},
